* Classic Compute
** Runs in your Azure subscription
** Access Modes
*** Standard
****_ Multiple users share cluster
****_ Lakeguard isolation between users
****_ Cost-efficient pooling
*** Dedicated
****_ Single user or group
****_ Full machine-level privileges
****_ Required for RDD, GPU, R, custom containers
** Cluster Modes
*** Multi-node
****_ Driver + worker nodes
****_ Horizontal scaling
****_ Production workloads
*** Single-node
****_ Driver only, no workers
****_ Small datasets, ML experimentation
****_ Can't scale horizontally
** Startup time
***_ 3-7 minutes
** Runtime management
***_ You select and manage Databricks Runtime version
***_ Manual upgrade (e.g. 13.3 LTS → 14.3 LTS)
@endmindmap
